Some corrections (you may later ask the licence creator for any corrections):

Partial pieces of the code are free to use, unless using a highly significant part of the code ( for example, a three line function that calculates all the physics in the code is more significant then a 500 line class that is just a box) or using it as an extension (meaining, to use it as a part of the 'front-end' and not 'back-end'), then you must credit the original creator as a Code/Library/General other software contributor in Contributor in the same area and as conspicuously as the original creator when contributing a modified version. (For dummies: no, you do not need to inherit the licence in this case)

When contributing a modified version of this product you are considered a contributor and shall be mentioned as a contributor in as such of a prominent place as the original creator, in all products deriving from your modification.

